        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 6 at 1:00PM EDT until June 6 at 1:30PM EDT by NWS Pittsburgh PA</headline>
        <description>SVRPBZ

The National Weather Service in Pittsburgh has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Fayette County in southwestern Pennsylvania...
South Central Westmoreland County in southwestern Pennsylvania...

* Until 130 PM EDT.

* At 100 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Scottdale,
or 6 miles north of Connellsville, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and small hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Connellsville, Mount Pleasant, Scottdale, Everson, Donegal, Acme
and Normalville.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds.</instruction>
